# UEC Image Automatic Signing Key <cdimage@ubuntu.com> — used by lib/vm.sh to
# verify the Ubuntu cloud image before it becomes the VM's root disk.
#
# Ubuntu does not sign each image. It signs one SHA256SUMS covering the whole
# release directory, with a detached SHA256SUMS.gpg; the image's authenticity is
# that signature plus its line in the signed file. Different shape from
# arch-boxes' per-image .sig, same invariant: no authentication, no VM.
#
# Fingerprint: D2EB44626FDDC30B513D5BB71A5D6C4C7DB87C81  (rsa4096, 2009-09-15)
#
# Corroborated out of band, because a fingerprint you fetched by fingerprint is
# only ever a tautology: the same fingerprint ships in Ubuntu's own
# ubuntu-keyring package (usr/share/keyrings/ubuntu-cloudimage-keyring.gpg),
# which comes from the archive rather than from cloud-images.ubuntu.com. That is
# a second publication channel agreeing — it is not a second cryptographic root,
# since the archive's own trust anchor travels in that same package.
